                        <interp inst="t18371127-name-870" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN COUCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coachman. On the 30th of November I was at Mr. Malcolm's house, in Warren-street, Charing-cross—the prisoner came in, and sat by my side—I went out, looked through a hole, and watched—I saw him take a pint pot and put it into his hat—he came out—I followed him, and called a policeman, who took it out of his hat—this is it—he appeared sober.</p>
